inn1.comm: good start, in that channel outside off stump. Not a lot of carry off the wicket and Matt Prior stoops to collect
again, there or thereabouts, a hint of uncertainty from the batsman
left alone more comfortably this time. Not a huge amount of pace off the pitch so far
a grimace from Anderson as this one fizzes through too. A bit of drizzle in the air as well now ...
outside off, left alone again. Gets to Prior on the second bounce
a snorting delivery to finish. Gayle leaves alone very uncertainly, and the ball just scrapes over the top of off
yikes, that was a bit wild! Pushed massively wide down leg side. No chance of cutting that off
not quite so loose, but still misdirected. A few nerves for Sidebottom. This is, after all, his first ODI for six years
much better, much tighter to the off stump. Excruciatingly tight, in fact. Good luck or good judgment? You decide
bat on ball at last, and this one is driven square
pushed down to long-on. Very mizzly weather out there now
takes the splice and flies safely through the vacant gully. Bit of late movement away from the left-hander there. Sidebottom is settling now
a swing and a miss. Just shaping away from the batsman, and taken at waist-height by Prior
fuller length, and squirted down to third man. Good recovery after a loose start to the over
shapes away from the batsman a fraction, guided down to third man. A productive region so far in this innings
good wheels from Jimmy. Puts it on the spot outside off, Gayle meets with a straight blade and jogs a single into the covers
signs of aggression from Smith. Charges down the pitch and has a big swing. Doesn't quite connect properly
angled into the pads, and bobbles away to the leg-side
fuller length, and firmly walloped with a lot of bottom hand. That was no half-volley, just a very well-judged shot
just sneaks down the leg-side. A tight call
in the channel outside off stump again, but nothing threatening
massive swish and a miss. Plenty of intent, little reward
good delivery, almost an attempted yorker, curving in late. Pushed watchfully down to mid-on
back outside off stump this time. Left alone with a big flourish
another wild swish. This one nipped away significantly though, and Gayle was barely in the same county by the time bat passed ball
fuller and speared into off stump, flicked in front of square on the leg-side, where Mascarenhas fields with a slide
Smith advances down the track again and has a dart, but Sidebottom's found some handy lateral movement in this over, and again the ball shoots past without any danger
pushed out to point
well, that one has been utterly spanked. Finally made contact with one of his massive hoons outside off stump, and this one clears the rope at extra cover by a good six yards
ouch. This one clobbers Gayle on the side of the knee as he shapes to play a one-footed pull. A moment of discomfort for Gayle, but he's a trooper.
just back of a length. Played cautiously this time
short again and a good connection, but fielded well in the covers
played firmly out to cover to complete the over.
outside off stump, left alone
good shape through the air, curving late. A misfield at mid-off gifts a single as Pietersen gets over-eager with a one-handed pick-up
great strike. Too much width, and Smith was down on one knee and cut that powerfully in front of point. Lovely shot, and Smith held his pose for the cameras too
nurdled down to third man
in the air for a little while, but there's no-one at gully, and third man cleans up. Good movement through the air now
inswinger to the left-hander this time. Played comfortably down to mid-off
more aggressive intent, a big mow across the line, but not a lot of bat on it
pitched on middle-and-leg, and worked square
short, and Gayle is into position for the pull, up on one leg and finding the gap
big appeal for lbw. Pitched outside the line and an inside-edge too. Quite close other than that
that's a lovely shot, and once again, England are punished for bowling too short on what is proving to be a batsman-friendly pitch. Clubbed through the covers, and Collingwood can't cut it off
good over, nine runs coming from it
pitched on middle and leg to start with, worked square.
lovely delivery, sliced across Gayle's bows like a liner through a rowing boat. Pitched on middle and leg and just eluded off stump
massive, massive heave at this one. Any connection would have disappeared in any direction. But he misses
he doesn't miss this one! That is monstrous. Hit it high on the bat and got underneath the ball as well, but no matter. It clears the long-on boundary by furlongs
on middle and leg again. Prodded back down the pitch

that one climbs off a good length, and raps Gayle on the thumb. Good response from Broad, but it's another run as the ball deflects down to third man

Given as leg-byes though
wide of the crease from around the wicket, Smith chops the ball down into his popping crease, deceived by the angle

Smith is gone, and that was a loose slash outside off stump. It was short and wide, and there to be clobbered, but Smith rushed the stroke and instead feathered the simplest of edges through to Prior. An important breakthrough for England
an ooh and an aah greets Chanderpaul at No. 3, driven to mid-off
played out to point
tidy work from Anderson, as Chanderpaul beds into his new position. Defended watchfully
beaten outside off. Lovely line
no more than a punch from Gayle, and a despairing Collingwood can't cut it off. The power in the last over, the finesse in this one
tucked off the hip to bring Chanderpaul onto strike
misdirected, speared down leg
tighter line now
curves away from the bat. Left alone
angled onto leg stump, clipped firmly, but straight to square leg
straighter, and driven with good intent, fielded with a tumble at cover
up there, a good length and an easy defence
leg-byes signalled as that one's rushed round
bottom edge off an attempted cut shot, didn't know where it had gone... but not the stumps, as he turned round to check
slightly leggy once again, and tucked off the hips behind square
better line - across the left hander and outside off stump, but shorter and cut off the back foot to the covers
pushed on to the back foot for an easy enough defensive
rushed through outside off - wide enough to leave and should be left because it's a good length. So it is
on off, rising and Chanderpaul gets off the mark with a mere caress down and forward off his back foot
straight, short, worked off the hip for a simple shuffle to midwicket
slightly curious... Broad held the ball with an inswinger grip (to the lefthander) and yet it swung away down the off side
now, that's a pearler - good line and length, prompting Chanderpaul to poke on the back foot, just missed out
wrong line there, down leg
casual down the off-side; just as casually left
too full outside off and another massive (Geoff) hoon, Gayle just extending his arms to launch that over wide long-off. Fabulous shot
Gayle goes to repeat the launch, looking to shoot over long-on, but was through the shot way too early, stopping on it, and sending an easy catch to Anderson who clings on at  mid-on
great welcome ball, outside off and sneaking through bat and pad
big shout for lbw, but definitely not out - missing off stick by another stump or so. Chanderpaul calls for a single, Samuels turns it down
tidy length, defended on the front foot
outside off, Sidebottom staying over by the way, defended outside off to round off a successful over for England
on leg, Chanderpaul strides forward to knock the ball easily through midwicket, some lovely timing
worked straight to the man at square
on off, defended down, squaring up
more good lines, defended forward
on middle-and-leg, but up there and Chanderpaul defends on one knee, crouching over to kill the bounce
outside off, run down well to third man
outside off, a thick outside edge, somewhat controlled, runs down to third man
outside off, worked to gully
pushed across him again, worked into the covers off the back foot
on middle, up there, defended forward
outside off and Samuels is off the mark with a single
poked away from the body, squared up and an outside edge flies tantalisingly near Prior's outstretched left glove
a direct hit from the shy from midwicket would have been close, there. It wasn't a direct hit, though
outside off, driven back to mid-off
outside off, driven back to mid-off. Again
wider outside off, poked an outside edge down safe
outside off, a touch shorter, and Samuels creeps across to defend on the back foot
outside off, a thick edge is controlled down to a wide third man
outside off, defended down
oh, nearly gets his man there, beating him outside the off stump
across the righthander, defended down
on leg, worked behind square for a quick single
outside off, a touch of inswing, Chanderpaul is happy just to leave it
on middle, driven forward off the front foot to midwicket for a very quick single
across the lefthander who fends down off the back foot with a very straight bat
steps out to meet the ball as it pitches just outside off and is nudged to mid-off
slower delivery, straight, up there, defended forward
comes forward and nearly, nearly shaves through a very fine edge
wristed off the front foot to short square leg
on leg, worked quickly down to short fine leg for a sneaky single
defended on the front foot this time
comes forward with attacking intent but has to check his desires, defending into the covers
cuts a bottom edge down in front of the keeper
creeps forward again, wields a forward defensive into the covers
outside off, worked to mid-off and there's no single possible
outside off, chops down a deliberate back foot defensive into the covers this time
worked square on the off side with Prior's exhortation to "Get on that" ringing loud in Bell's ears
outside off, rising, deflated by Samuels with an effective defensive
on middle-and-leg, this time the "Get on that" screeched huskily (if that's not oxymoronic) to mid-on
outside edge, but wouldn't have carried to slip, Chanderpaul slicing a drive and taking his top hand off
defended on the back foot
driven to mid-off
a nudge to start my stint, Chanderpaul punching it off his hip
good line, this, outside his off stump and Samuels is slightly hurried into an off-side push
an ugly, bottom-handed spoon over midwicket - or that was his intention, anyway - and it just evaded mid-on
swinging into Samuels who tries to work it to leg, and misses
but he connects with it this time, knocking it to leg for a quick single
"get on it," is the call from Prior as Chanderpaul works this to leg for a single
swinging into Samuels who defends, solidly
the wrong line, drifting into his pads and it's worked for another single
neat stroke, coming right forward and punching it through short extra cover
Prior screams and wails at the fielder in the covers, informing him he had better stop the ball or else
punched out to cover to end the over
swinging into Samuels who defends off the back foot. Good line
very deftly played indeed. Collingwood gave him a little extra room, but Samuels late-cut it down to third man with silky ease
on off stump, Chanderpaul pushes this out to cover
nudged off his hip
good line and length, Chanderpaul forced to defend
stroked out to extra cover to end the over
excellent line, angling across Chanderpaul who leaves it alone. Excellent take from the helmeted Prior
left alone once again
rubbish ball, equally dismal shot - wide of Chanderpaul who tried to cut, but hit it with about as much power as an asthmatic wasp
clumped, again with asthmatic intent, nowhere
left alone outside off. Good take from Prior
nicely played this time, just turning it through midwicket
Chanderpaul tries to smack this over midwicket, but gets a thick inside/under edge
good length, Chanderpaul can't work this away
a huge shout from Collingwood, getting louder and louder as he goes - back-stepping like Michael Jackson in his hey day. The umpire is distinctly unimpressed, and it looks like a good decision too
cut hard but a brilliant stop at point prevents a run
ooh very close! Very, very close indeed, angling across Chanderpaul who fishes at it and misses
beautiful shot, flicked through midwicket with panache. He just moved across his stumps a touch
good line again, and Samuels can't make anything of it
defended on the back foot
swinging into Samuels who again punches it back to the bowler
very well bowled indeed, almost squaring Samuels up here. Played back to the bowler again
but he loses his line here, drifting it down the leg side and it's sponged for a single to midwicket
crabbed out to cover who shies at the stumps, but Chanderpaul's safely home
ooh that bounced, takes Chanderpaul's glove and it flies down to third man
dropped - a difficult chance but if anyone could've taken it, Collingwood could. Punched back to him, Collingwood moved to his left and appeared to get both hands to it but spilled it
cut down to third man
chopped out to cover
drifting down the leg side, Samuels was desperate to smudge this over midwicket

and he's got him! Has he? A beautiful outswinger drawing Samuels into a drive, and Prior whips off the bails. But replays suggest that Samuels' foot was down at the point of the bails being whipped off. Or was it? Up, down, up, down...and he's received the benefit of the doubt from the third umpire. Fair enough, if you ask me. Lovely piece of cricket from Collingwood though
punched down the ground
ooh, good leave from Chanderpaul outside his off stump. No swing for the bowler here
Prior says "oi-ay", further adding new words to the dictionary, and for that we should be grateful. Left alone once again outside the off stump
another leave from Chanderpaul; another new word from Prior. "Goy-eh" this time
Chanderpaul connects with it this time, cutting it backward of square for a nothing
defended on the back foot
ooh close! Samuels came forward to defend, missed it, the ball wobbling through to Prior and just evading his off-stump
on the back foot, it's cut hard behind point but again he can't find a boundary
breaking news: a four. Great shot it was, too, Chanderpaul just lifting it up and over long-on for four
magnificent stroke - the balance was the key there, Chanderpaul again lifting Collingwood but this time over midwicket. Beautifully placed and timed
nudged to leg
lovely ball on middle-and-off which is firmly punched back to the bowler
nudged out to cover
swinging into the left-hander who can't get it past cover
ever so slightly shorter, but Chanderpaul's cut to a short third man offers him no chance of a run
very wide indeed, Chanderpaul did well to reach that, and Collingwood fields brilliantly in the covers to prevent a single
pumped to the rarely-spotted Yardy at mid-on for a single
elegantly guided down to third man
short and wide, and that's smashed away with a flash of the blade, up and over point
short again and clobbered in front of square this time. Samuels is starting to up his tempo
full and straight, and defended with a hollow 'clunk' down into the popping crease
a fraction of width, carved into the covers to keep the strike rotating
short - too short - and that's excellently swatted over backward square. Samuels was briefly on the front foot for that one, but rocked back well
that's a belting strike. Took his front foot out of the line, opened his shoulders and swished an attempted yorker straight over the bowler's head
clipped off the toes, rolls gently past the square leg umpire
rocks onto the back foot, hint of turn but a touch short, guided in front of point
leg-stump line, and holds its line. Samuels can't connect
big appeal, but that one was definitely sliding down leg. Good drift into the right-hander though
pushed out to cover, nicely fielded
slightly squared up, but shuffled off the legs
good wicket-to-wicket delivery to start things off, just angling in towards leg stump
off stump line this time. Keeper standing up
squeezed uncomfortably out to point. Once again, a lack of pace is doing the trick
big appeal as Samuels overbalances while trying to clip a leg-stump delivery. A late decision to remove the bails. Another near-miss for the chancy Samuels
onto the front foot and defended. No width at all being offered here by the steady Mascarenhas
hustled single through and a bit of a chance for a run-out. The shy comes in from the covers and just misses the stumps at the non-striker's end
full and floated up to leg stump. Defended
lots of dancing at the crease from Samuels, as he eventually steers this to point
a bit of an 'ooh' all round as Samuels is squared up
clipped off the pads
looped right up into the blockhole, Chanderpaul waits and clips this one behind square
speared down leg
pushed firmly into the covers.
well, that could have been the breakthough, but Bell just doesn't have the hangtime at backward point to reach an airy steer. Nor can Owais Shah, sliding futilely at third man
good wicket-to-wicket line. Excellent control from Mascarenhas
carved firmly out to point, but fielded with a bobble
driven back along the pitch. Good bowling
"ohhohohohohohohoaaa" exclaims Matt Prior, as well he might, as this one is defended in front of middle and off
pushed into the leg-side
turned around the corner. The slower bowlers are keeping things tight for England
clipped out to midwicket and that's yet another half-century for Chanderpaul - six in all internationals. He is a machine.
more rotation. West Indies keeping their cool
squirted into the covers
another single completes a steady over. Now then, at what point do they apply some humpty?
firm clump down the ground, well intercepted by Anderson on the boundary's edge
slower ball, and patiently pushed out to the cover sweeper
right on the money once again, nothing for Chanderpaul to do but push past point and scamper another single
right up in the blockhole, not quite a yorker length, but defended nonetheless
pushed into the leg-side and fielded by the bowler
that's the shot we've been expecting. Enough of this respectful treatment. Nothing much wrong with the delivery, but Samuels got underneath and cleared the long-on boundary by a distance
looped onto a length, and Chanderpaul picks the gap to bring his partner onto strike
clipped off the pads, but can't beat the man on the 45
leg-side delivery, squeak of alarm from Prior as he senses a stumping chance
more squeaking from Prior. Nothing doing
driven back down the ground, fielded above his head by Yardy
turned out to square leg. Another tidy over
ideal line and length. Nudged respectfully back up the pitch
strays a touch onto leg stump, but no pace to work with, and square leg tidies up
extra lift in front of middle, and nurdled down to fine leg
West Indies still dealing with singles here. This one is placed in the off side and an easy one
easy again. Clipped into the leg side
good swooping from Bell at backward point, and that's the end of an excellent spell from Dimitri Mascarenhas. Just two boundaries conceded in ten overs. And one of those was a half-chance
angled down the leg-side
clipped out to midwicket. This is all very, very one-paced. Sensible batting though
another nudge into the leg-side, and that's a leisurely half-century. Well batted
eased again into the leg-side
turned off the hip
cool as you like. This is pedestrian stuff
poor delivery, down leg, but a top shot, hooking that down and round through fine leg
tried to pull round, failed - mistiming, there
outside off, cut into the ground
width, and worked over cover
tried to scythe that to mid-on, much like my fiance wielding his light sabre at the Star Wars exhibition yesterday
...unlike that wide, a naughty stray
driven almost on the run, Chanderpaul easing into the knock to cover and setting off immediately
outside off, worked into the covers
a quick single to mid-on where Collingwood can't return a direct shy
cue circus music as Shah and Sidebottom on the boundary juggle and fail to keep it in
on middle, turned off the hips for a quick single... ah, two in fact
lovely reverse sweep behind square. Premeditated as these shots often are; easy wrists, too
reaches outside leg to drive to mid-on
horrible full toss, frankly, swatted through the covers
short this time, miscued pull shot rolls round to Mascarenhas at fine leg to bring up the 200
on leg and full, dug out well to mid-on; there was little room to manoeuvre there
outside off and that's a belter of a cover drive, lifted off the back foot and the base of the bat
outside off, cut away through backward point. Top timing, and that runs all the way, smoothly
driven over the top, and straight - cracking shot
outside off, crouches into a drive to cover
outside off, driven to the covers
lashed off the back foot through point, moving his front foot out of the way
oh, a chance to mid-off there as that's sailed high, but Pietersen was nowhere need it - Collingwood called for it and nearly took it over his shoulder
driven to mid-off, good timing
driven to mid-off
outside off, flashed away with a thumping cover drive
waits to play late off the knee, with a square drive through point
attempted slower ball scythed across the line high and over long-off
Chanderpaul falls over trying to reach that wide - think Del Boy and the bar in Only Fools and Horses. Crash.
a good effort by Anderson in the deep, having to dive forward as Chanderpaul laces over towards long-on
on middle, whipped away on one knee in front of square
taken from outside off with a strike-stealing drive to mid-on
outside off, crashed off the back foot towards the rope where Bell does well to cut it off
up there, defended on the front foot
wider, driven out to the cover boundary where it's well cut off by Cook, and don't the crowd love it
worked down off the back foot to third man
outside off, cut off the back foot to point
slow bouncer, a simple catch for Sidebottom at gully, Samuels popping that one up to him
brilliance from Chanderpaul - it was so nearly a perfect delivery outside off and somehow he manages to sweep on the front foot off his toes
full toss on the knee, stunned to mid-on for a quick single
pushed up and defended back down
eased out square and quickly returned
and that's it, worked to midwicket to bring up his seventh ODI ton
short, straight and too high
over the boards - no mean hit - with a huge straight thump over long-on and Anderson pays for that extra ball
worked out through the covers for two more runs
low full toss, Mascarenhas just about fashions a long barrier at mid-off
an attempted yorker slips, too high, and clatters into the pad. A big shout goes up, and the umpire has to give it; that would have hit middle-and-off halfway up
down the leg side and Morton bends over in trying to defend
up there, dug out to mid-on where it's winged back in
driven out to long-off
turned off the legs to square
on leg, well worked out full to fine leg
sprayed down leg, a (pretty) wide
beautiful shot, timed off the hips up and over midwicket, just a flick, really, but that's flown
low full toss, drilled wide of long-on, good timing and placement, there
on leg, dabbed down to midwicket for a quick single
pushed square and Chanderpaul is content to give Morton the strike
slower ball, flashed high and straight down the ground, where Bell takes the catch well, in front of his body
on leg, flicked to midwicket for a quick single
outside off and that's sent high, but safe, over to deep cover
low full toss, driven out to mid-on
good delivery, slower and outside off, swiped over
slower delivery again, late cut down to third man to bring them to 278 for 5

inn2.comm: and he starts with a wideish ball outside Cook's off stump, swinging wider - the umpire's arms remain rooted beside him though
excellent delivery this time though, cutting back into Cook who is late on it, the ball spitting off the pitch
and this goes the other way! Great start for Rampaul, knocking one off the seam and Cook plays and misses
again this cuts away from the left hander who leaves it well alone - warily and cautiously
very firmly forward this time from Cook, defending it with a pleasing clunk of the bat on the front foot
well played, cut straight into the ground and although he didn't appear to time it too well, it was neatly placed
firmly blocked out off the back foot

an ugly mow over the top, Prior hasn't got "all" of it, as the expression goes, miscuing it over Sammy's head at mid-off. And there's a near calamitous piece of running when Cook wanted two...but the throw was wide
Cook steps to leg but is a bit late on this cut, chopping it down to the off side
clunked out to the off side
firmly defended on the front foot from Cook this time
nudged out to cover - quick from Powell - and they scamper a single
on his leg stump, Cook comes forward, poking at it - as though pointing to something on the pitch
Rampaul gives him width here and Cook unleashes his favourite cut, timing it nicely but straight to point
nudged off his hips. "No no, wait there" is the call from Cook
lovely bowling, drifting this across Cook who is drawn into a back-foot poke. Airy, wafty stroke, lacking conviction
but it's down the leg side this time and wided
just short of a length, Cook paddles it around the corner
left alone outside off
down the leg side, Cook flicks it off his toes down to fine leg
that's very nicely bowled - a good length, rising onto Cook but it was wide enough for him to angle it down to third man
fast, but too wide. And wided.
cracking delivery and impressive bounce from Powell, who is now steaming in. It just left Prior at the last moment, rising onto him at chest height
but Prior leaves this well alone now outside the off stump
turned around the corner but straight to square leg
left alone outside off
on middle-and-leg, Cook squirts it back to the bowler
magnificent shot - a firm, elegant on-drive for four. No follow-through or extravagant flourish; just a solid punch for four. Class
again, very well played indeed - it wasn't that short but it was wide, and Cook pulled it with a heavy bottom hand through midwicket
on off stump this time. It's blocked out
again, lovely stroke from Cook - coming confidently forward onto the front foot, driving it elegantly down the ground to long-off this time
drifting into his pads, it bobbles out to leg
gone! Poor stroke. It was wide, he went after it and tried to loft it over mid-off's head but couldn't quite clear Edwards, who timed his jump perfectly
ooh that's a nasty one, though Bell came shimmying down the pitch - as is Bell Mach II's wont - and it rapped him on the hip
a nudge to leg to get off the mark
defended on the back foot
down the leg side, and it's nudged further to leg for a single
Bell drops this dead into the off side and screams - literally, a scream, like a slaughtered pig - no
an ugly smudge across the line, but it's effective enough and they get a single
there goes Bell, walking across his crease like an Earl marching across his land, angling this down to third man
flicked down to fine leg
an elegant punch on the front foot, but straight back to the bowler
and he's given him! Bell was back in his crease, the ball jagging back massively onto the right hander and rapping him on the pads on off stump
ooh and another corker from Rampaul, cutting it off the seam and it, in turn, almost cuts Pietersen in half
straight, full, fast and Prior punches it to mid-on
a studious defensive stroke on the front foot. Again - a good line here
wild and woolly, down the leg side
bang. A magnificent shot, pulling this ball outside the off stump over midwicket for six
cut down to third man
Pietersen's off the mark here, pushing this out to cover and scampering through
a full toss, pumped into the covers to finish the over
lovely stroke, standing tall and driving to extra cover. Terrific stroke for no run
an even better shot, straighter this time and driving it to mid-off. But straight to mid-off
good grief, that's a heck of a stroke, skipping down the pitch and on-driving him for four. Quite beautifully played
nudged off his pads, but no run on offer there
defended out to cover
that's nicely bowled from Rampaul, attacking his stumps and it's defended back to the bowler
Prior skips down the pitch but Rampaul sees him coming and sends down a slower ball which he defends
ooh well bowled, drawing the batsman forward and it's squirted off a thick outside edge down to third man
off the pads, but he can't make anything of it
another beautiful drive from Prior who on-drives it...but straight to mid-on
short, Prior comes down the pitch before realising he has to defend
well bowled! A slower ball which completely deceived him
down the leg side, and not wided...
nudged calmly into the leg-side, and they trot through for a single
outside off stump, and Prior climbs into a drive, but the ball goes no further than his feet. Still, they get one out of it
onto the front foot and pushed out to wide mid-off. "Yeah, yeah, yeah" is the call, and rightly so
drawn forward again, defended out to cover
lovely strike, a much more forceful shot and that whistles through the covers. Big stride, and excellent followthrough. Proper kreekeet, as Sir Geoff might say
defended with a loud "no!"
banged in short and Pietersen shapes to duck. Hardly needs to in the end, as the ball is far too high to trouble him
big stride down the pitch and a statement of intent from Pietersen. Driven back to the bowler, but signs are that he wants to get on with it
width outside off stump, and a big slash down to third man. Definitely in a hurry
well, that's remarkable. Prior got right underneath that, a nine-iron down to the boundary's edge. And the ball stopped dead upon landing. It's soft out there
clipped out to the leg-side
that's a lovely ball, full and fast and Prior is left groping outside off stump
stepped across and worked into the leg side. A hasty single as mid-on runs round to tidy up
Prior opens his shoulders and attempts to flog Rampaul through the covers. Plenty of intent from England's batsmen right now, not a lot of return just yet
way down the leg side. Clouds are building up on the horizon I fear
another good stride and worked into the leg side
driven firmly into the off side, and a pretty average attempt to intercept the ball at cover. Pietersen's first boundary
strays down the leg side but not called as Pietersen had stepped well across his stumps. Almost passed over leg stump itself
another big stride. England are getting forward to the ball well, ready to pounce on anything a fraction loose

nothing loose there! That's a massive wicket, and once again, Pietersen was looking to come forward. In the end he yorked himself as he looked to whip through midwicket. Full credit to Rampaul who held his nerve, and his length
left well alone outside off
dabbed into the covers and Prior was through for a single almost before the ball left the bat. England will need more of that urgency if they are to dig themselves out of this hole
short and tucked into the ribs. But Edwards oversteps in his eagerness
clipped off the pads, Ramdin does well to scoop the ball up with a tumble
Shah is off the mark with a nudge into the leg-side
short. And quick. That one fizzed through as Prior turned turtle
onto the toes, and steered down to third man
Prior resumes with a confident steer past the diving point. Third man runs round to field
more positive intent, as this one is driven into the covers and they hustle through for a single. Prior makes his ground moments before the shy from cover hits his stumps
outside off and nibbling off the seam. Shah plays an inelegant defensive prod, but effective nonetheless
strays onto the pads and dabbed to midwicket
on a leg-stump line once again, but Prior can't work this past short midwicket
ambitious heave across the line, but the ball keeps low and scuds through to the keeper
a fraction short of a length, Shah is hurried into a defensive back-foot push
perfect line and length, wicket-to-wicket delivery, defended stoutly in front of off stump
that's a snorter, and West Indies are a bit miffed at this one, as the ball flicks Shah's back arm as it fizzes past the gloves. Correct decision, but Shah indicated what had happened
short again, and swift. Shah raises his gloves in defence, and turns this one behind square
banged in and that explodes off the pitch and way over Denesh Ramdin's despairing leap. He's pumped up at the moment. Maybe a little too pumped
fuller length, outside off, and this one is pushed awkwardly to point.
from one pace extreme to the other. Smith just dobbles this onto a bail-kissing length, and Shah waits in position to defend
drawn forward, defended again
a bit more width, dabbed out to point without much power
flicked around the corner
drawn forward and defended
dropped into the off side and another scampered single. This is becoming a very well-paced innings from Prior. It needs to be
full length, and fast. Hint of width and Prior uses the pace to glide another single to third man
full length, slower delivery - Edwards rolled the fingers in the delivery, like an offbreak. Shah can't put bat on ball
much quicker delivery. Short and fast, and Shah ducks
on the back foot, waits for the ball to come to him and steers into the covers
a bit of width, and that one is slashed greedily - it flies safe through the vacant second/third slip, and is fielded with a tumble at third man
strays onto the pads, whipped down to fine leg.
a self-referential curse as Smith spears this one down the leg-side
straighter and worked into the leg side
full and straight again. Shah steps back and nurdles a single to fine leg
looked like an offbreak action for that one. Either way, met with a straight bat
clipped in front of square, an easy two as the boundary sweeper runs round to tidy up

dropped. Big squeaks of alarm as Prior inside-edges into - and straight out of - Ramdin's gloves. Poor cricket from Powell who hits the stumps with a shy, but everyone is still appealing and the batsmen take overthrows
a let-off there for Prior. Can he capitalise?
a fraction of width, and worked down to third man
a big stride and a bigger thwack, as Bravo fields this ball with his injured ankle! The physio will be doing his nut as Bravo hobbles away
driven firmly down to long-off
defended with a dead bat, and a good sharp call for a single. More of those are what England need
squared up as he tries to come forward and work this through midwicket. Bravo stoops in his followthrough to field a leading edge
elegant stride, but ineffective. Point fields
defended on the front foot this time
more defensive stuff.. and yet they eke out a single
tight ball, and that's a necessary defensive
ooh, missed a run out by a sliver - at the non-striker's end
lovely line, Shah has nothing to play with - apart from a bat, and he defends down
touch of width this time, allowing a touch of manoeuvrability; a poke down behind point
on leg, easily worked off the pads through midwicket and it fair races away down the hill, it does, to bring up the 100
up there, on off, driven to mid-off
outside off, dinked behind point but there's a quick call of "Wait". And so they do
width outside off, run down to third man, thoughts of a second
worked in front of square
shorter delivery, rising up on off, fended back down off the back foot
good length, forcing a back-foot defensive
pushed off the back foot for a quick single
swept to the fielder behind square, got away with a poor delivery
paddled just behind square
on off, back of a length, driven on the front foot into the on-side
worked to wide mid-on and a misfield by Morton allows a second, nay, a third
on middle-and-leg, swished to midwicket
driven out to mid-on, another dot
good delivery, up there, but Prior does well to squeeze out to cover to bring up his first fifty in ODIs
a touch of hostility there, with a sharp delivery that rises and demands to be defended down on the back foot
up there, turned to leg, straight to the fielder
defended this time - good bowling from Edwards
testing delivery, rising and has Shah hopping up and then out of the way as the ball shoots through over his shoulder
quick delivery, turned well with the wrists but still pops up and over long leg, a bit of Pietersenesque improvisation
doesn't work this time - a leading edge as Prior was looking over the leg-side again, finds Smith at midwicket, with a simple chance
outside off, driven off the back foot to gully
defended into the covers
outside off, driven on the front foot to the covers
close call there at the non-striker's end, but nevertheless the umpire doesn't need a replay
defended a high-riser on the back foot
worked to short midwicket
comes forward to press a quick single into the covers
straight bouncer, very well directed - Collingwood only just managed to sway under that at the last minute
plumb as you like, and West Indies do like - that's a very big wicket for them. Collingwood trapped straight, the ball pitching on off and coming back and would have rocked middle
outside off, he shuffles over to drive into the covers
creeps over in his awkward Yardy way and leaves as that one flies past his shouldered arms
hoisted high with an unexpected chip shot off the base of his bat, landed in front of midwicket
worked into midwicket
a quick single shuffled forward
defended off the back foot, with a trap into the off-side
pitches on leg, and cuts the ball across the left hander, who doesn't drive to his liking
on off, jabbed down straight
short and Shah hooks that off his face to square, with plenty of time to control the shot
worked to mid-off
outside off, worked straight to point off the back foot
width outside off, handy boundary with a late cut way behind point, the third man coming across but his slide is in vain
slower ball, well watched and defended down off the back foot
on off, again well watched, and played to mid-off, but the asking rate is moving up
defended on the back foot
another dot.. England can't afford these
a flinging underarm shy on the dive nearly has Shah... but not quite
outside off, wafted into the covers
worked to the covers
worked to the covers once more, this time there's a single but West Indies are slowing applying the squeeze
outside off, cut straight to Smith at gully
pitches on middle-and-off, stabbed down into the covers
outside off, Yardy can't generate much power on it, and clunks a drive forward, Bravo nearly gets him with the return
Yardy has a very open stance, starting from outside leg and creeping over, this time to defend
outside off, driven to the covers for a quick single
up there, no room to do anything but defend
played back to the bowler
full and straight, punched back to the bowler once more
and Yardy goes for a more expansive cover drive this time
an ugly smote across the line from Shah who stepped outside leg, slapping it through midwicket
short this time and the Yardstick pulls it around the corner, without timing
swinging into the left-hander on his off stump, Yardy plays it back to the bowler
authoritatively pulled from Shah, standing tall - a touch of his mentor, Mohammad Azharuddin in that stroke
Yardy drives to nowhere and abandons the car in a field
stroked out to cover
Shah shuffles across his stumps and defends
firmly blocked out on the front foot
and Gayle's missed a run out! Well well well. Shah punched it to him at mid-on and Gayle, just a few metres from the stumps, tried to throw them down but somehow missed
punched again to mid-on who shies at the stumps
magnificently struck. He absolutely laced that through extra cover
nibbled to the leg side for a single
solidly blocked out off the back foot
shot: a short-arm pull behind square - a flick, more than anything - over the vacant fine leg for six. Intelligent batting, this
flicked down to fine leg again for four. Shah on the march here as the rain comes down
brilliantly timed from Yardy, flaying his hands at it outside off and cutting it behind point. Sammy was quick and athletic in the deep, though, saving four at third man
a quick call of "yep" Yardy as Shah turns this behind square to fine leg for a single
ooh and he's hit him in the chest. A brute of a ball, rising up onto Yardy who took his eye off it, the ball cannoning into his ribs
cut to Rampaul down at third man who slides to his left and, after playing monkey tennis with the ball, eventually flings it back in
pushed off his hip
that was quick! Very, very quick bouncer which Yardy simply nodded out of its way. Called a wide for height
nudged off his pads for a single behind square
clumped into the covers but Yardy can't time this
a beautiful turn of the wrists, pulling this through midwicket
slightly less beautiful shot from Yardy though - a furious slap through midwicket, wielding his bat like a middle-aged banker wheeling out his lawnmower for the first mow of the season
clunked into the covers with farmyard elegance
a slower ball on off stump, nicely bowled but Shah picked it, dropping it out to cover
defended on the back foot
pushed out to cover
Yardy's standing a good foot outside his leg stump, trying to put the bowler off, so Rampaul fires it down the leg side. And Yardy misses.
Yardy clunks this back to the bowler ineffectually
neatly clipped off his toes to a short midwicket who sends a scurrying Yardy back into his crease with a ferocious throw at the stumps
and there's the fifty partnership from 61 balls. Well done everyone.
mis-slapped to mid-off for a zero
it's a four! The crowd are alive again as Yardy nudges this down to fine leg
played out to the off side
oh dear. Yardy, looking for the big shot over midwicket, mistimes this pull and skies it to deep midwicket who doesn't move a muscle, taking a simple catch
a slower ball which Shah skipped down the pitch to meet, but was deceived by the lack of pace and ended up scewing it to cover
an exaggerated walking defence
knocked back to Bravo who tries to throw down the stumps but forgets to let go of the ball
got him! Rampaul sends it shorter and wider, tempting Shah into a pull but he gets a thin bottom edge through to the wicketkeeper
played out to cover
swinging into the left-hander who defends
tickled around the corner for a single
Mascarenhas tries to whack this through the covers, but can't time it
a more crunching drive this time but there's a sweeper out on the boundary edge
cracked on the front foot to mid-off, Rampaul I think it was who dived over the top
pushed out to cover
short of a length, Broad pulls it to deep square leg
neatly angled to point
Bravo Dwayne - bet you've never heard that pun before, have you? - an excellent inswinging slower ball which Broad is rather late on
slightly lazy from Gayle at mid-off. A chip from Broad ballooning over his head, and he got a hand to it while back-stepping...but couldn't cling on
excellent delivery, swinging into Mascarenhas outside his off stump. He plays; he misses
Mascarenhas flicks at this outside the off stump, and again misses it
clunked back to the bowler
defended on the back foot
short of a length, Mascarenhas tries to pull it but mistimes it to Powell at mid-on who takes a comfortable catch
Sidebottom guides it past third slip to third man
full length, and driven out to cover. A hint of swing maybe?
short, but not very short. Pulled, but not very effectively. Fielded, but pretty hopelessly. Morton at mid-on picks up, shies, and overthrows is the upshot
nudged away for another single
short, and that's hammered up and over midwicket. Excellent forceful strike. It's a little too late, however
short and pulled again, but that one is high on the bat and dribbles out into the leg-side
full-toss and elegantly driven, but well fielded with a tumble at mid-off
full toss, swinging away in every sense of the word. A lovely flowing strike, clean through the gap in the covers. Sidebottom is running free at the moment

fuller length, not quite a yorker. Sidebottom crouches and, with a keen eye, steers out to point. They aimed for a quick single but the third umpire shows a squeakingly close decision. Excellent work from Dwayne Smith and its all over bar the self-indulgent guitar solo
short, and clobbered through the covers off the back foot. Lovely strike
dropped. Broad attempted an action replay and Bravo at point dives but can't cling on with one hand. Good effort though
short, and Anderson sways out of the line
shorter still, Anderson ducks. England need 79. And a miracle
full length, just outside off. Nicely timed through the gully off the back foot
straighter, and driven up to mid-on
square driven, and effectively
short again. Anderson sways again. He's happy to stick it out in a futile cause
slightly fuller, but still short, if you see what I mean. Driven out to point off the back foot
full this time, and Anderson is drawn into a bona fide swing-and-a-miss
another nicely timed square drive off the back foot. A misfield at point gifts a single
he likes that shot. Up on his toes and cut/driving straight to point.
short, too short
short again, and steered off the back foot. More sloppiness in the field, but it's forgivable. West Indies have administered a righteous whupping today
attempted yorker, well watched and squirted down to third man
right idea, wrong execution. Attempted yorker comes out as a full-toss. And goes through to the keeper
another full-toss, and fielded in the covers
okay, I take that back. That was worth hanging around for - a baseball slog over the infield, one bounce on the rope at long-on. Marvellous connection
carved through point to the boundary sweeper
short, and sails through to the keeper via a no-stroke-offered
massive appeal for lbw, and it looked pretty close. Full length, but swinging away late and would have missed off. Good call umpire
jogs back for the second to complete the over
dead-batted like a vampire slayer. Watchful stuff in a lost cause
swish. Miss. Oooh
another bouncer. Anderson getting some medicine after a touch of argy-bargy with Runako Morton earlier today
watchful stuff from Jimmy. If this was a Test match I'd be gripped
steered backward of point

full length outswinger, Anderson is drawn into the stroke, and the thin edge is pouched by Denesh Ramdin. West Indies have won a handsome victory, as Edwards strikes with the final ball of his spell. Excellent effort from him, both here and at Lord's
